South Korea Stocks: Korea Zinc, OCI, Samsung Securities, STX

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-04-15T06:43:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/south-korea-stocks-hyundai-securities-korea-zinc-stx-pan.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in South Korea trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close in  Seoul .  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  was little changed at 2,140.50, ending the
week 0.6 percent higher. It’s the fifth straight weekly advance
for the gauge, which closed at a record high of 2,141.06
yesterday.  Brokerages: Samsung Securities Co. (016360 KS) rose 2.4
percent to 81,900 won. Daewoo Securities Co. (006800 KS) climbed
1.8 percent to 22,600 won. Woori Investment & Securities Co.
(005940 KS) gained 0.8 percent to 20,050 won.  “The market is showing an uptrend, boosting expectations
that trading value will increase,” said Cho Soung Kyung, an
analyst at KTB Securities Co. “Valuations of brokerage firms
are also very attractive.”  Korea Zinc Co. (010130 KS), which produces gold and silver,
jumped 2.9 percent to 442,000 won. Silver futures topped $42 an
ounce, extending a rally to the highest since 1980. Gold also
rose yesterday.  OCI Co. (010060 KS), a South Korean maker of polysilicon,
climbed 5.5 percent to a record 533,000 won. The shares gained
on speculation first-quarter profit may exceed consensus
estimates, said Park Yeon Ju, an analyst with Daewoo Securities
Co.  STX Pan Ocean Co. (028670 KS),  South Korea ’s biggest bulk
carrier, retreated 2 percent to 9,280 won, the lowest close
since April 1, 2009. The Baltic Dry Index, a measure of
commodity shipping costs, fell 1.1 percent to 1,309 points,
according to the  Baltic Exchange  in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
